<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">GG words appear constantly in Scrabble because the -GGING pattern is one of the most productive suffixes in English. Every verb ending in G doubles it before adding -ING: DIG→DIGGING, BEG→BEGGING, NAG→NAGGING. This makes GG one of the easiest double-letter combinations to play, and with 3 G tiles in the bag, opportunities arise often.</p>

